synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involved mixing metal ruthenium and ruthenium dioxide at a 1:1 molar ratio, reacting the mixture at 1400°C under reduced pressure, precipitating the gas-cooled product at 900°C, pulverizing the bulk product to obtain 5 μm powder, coating the cerium-lanthanum oxide composite with carbon via thermal CVD treatment, and finally combining the resulting composite with lithium hydride to produce a negative electrode material for a nonaqueous electrolyte secondary battery with an 8% lithium doping amount.
